        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on ‘</span><span class=\"english\">The Impacts of Loneliness’</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">within 10 sentences.</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">The Impacts of Loneliness</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Loneliness is a powerful human experience that often arises from the absence of love and care. It creates an emptiness that goes beyond physical isolation and touches the depths of the heart. Without emotional support, life feels cold and burdensome. This sense of being unwanted or neglected silently damages self-confidence and happiness. Loneliness often forces individuals to build imaginary comforts to hide their inner pain. Such illusions may bring temporary relief but eventually reveal the deeper void. It highlights the universal human need for connection, affection, and belonging. Material things cannot replace the warmth of relationships, nor can they heal the wounds of neglect. Only compassion, empathy, and kindness from others can ease the burden of this silent suffering. Thus, loneliness stands as both a reminder of human vulnerability and a call for greater understanding in human relationships.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest Mark --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------09 Marks </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) For Title (</span><span class=\"english\">The Impacts of Loneliness</span><span class=\"english\">) </span><span class=\"english\">-----------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> --------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Loneliness, often triggered by the absence of love and care, is a profound human experience that transcends physical isolation and touches deeply into the heart.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(C) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">Emotional Support and Life's Coldness</span><span class=\"english\">) (Any 06) </span><span class=\"english\">-------------06 Marks                                                                                                                                                                          </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Without emotional support, life can feel empty, cold, and burdensome.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Feeling unwanted or neglected harms self-confidence and inner happiness.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Loneliness often leads people to create imaginary comforts to escape emotional pain.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">These illusions offer short-term relief but cannot fill the deeper emptiness.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Every human being needs genuine connection, affection, and a sense of belonging.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Material possessions can’t replace love or emotional warmth.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Compassion, empathy, and kindness from others are essential to heal emotional suffering.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(D) Conclusion ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Loneliness serves as a reminder of human vulnerability and a call for deeper understanding in human relationships.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">For every 3 spelling/grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2</span><span class=\"english\">. We will consider up to 12 sentences. However, if a student writes more than 12 sentences but less than double (20 sentences), 50% of the deserving marks must be deducted. If it becomes double (20 sentences), full marks have to be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">Comment: Write within 10 sentences.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3. </span><span class=\"english\">Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Comment: Write within single/one para)</span><span class=\"english\">.</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">4.</span><span class=\"english\"> For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark.</span></p>"
